The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Birla Corp shareholder files petition

 Calcutta, Dec. 21 (PTI): A Chennai-based shareholder in Birla Corporation Ltd today moved a petition before Calcutta High Court seeking removal of Rajendra S. Lodha as director of the MP Birla group flagship.

 Shareholder P. Madhavan, while submitting his petition before Justice Indira Banerjee, claimed that Lodha had not obtained the requisite share qualification for holding the directors post within the statutory period of two months.

 According to the companies act, a certain percentage of shares has to be registered in the name of a director within two months of the persons election to the post, he submitted. 




